    <page id="intro">
    	<title>Getting Started</title>
    	<group>
	    	<link id="newUser" style-id="left"
	    		url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/runAction?pluginId=org.thanlwinsoft.languagetest&amp;class=org.thanlwinsoft.languagetest.eclipse.wizards.NewUserProjectAction&amp;id=org.thanlwinsoft.languagetest.NewUserProjectAction">
	    		<img id="newUserIcon" src="../../icons/newUser.png" alt="New User"/>
	    		<text>1. Add a new user. </text>
	    	</link>
	    	<text>You will be asked first for your own language, then the language you want to learn. Please specify the script (e.g. Latin for English) and a Font if necessary.</text>
	    	<link id="newModule" style-id="left"
	    		url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/runAction?pluginId=org.thanlwinsoft.languagetest&amp;class=org.thanlwinsoft.languagetest.eclipse.wizards.NewLangModuleAction&amp;id=org.thanlwinsoft.languagetest.NewLangModuleAction">
	    		<text>2. Create a Language Module. </text>
				<img id="newModuleIcon" src="../../icons/newModule.png" alt="New Module"/>
	    	</link>
	    	<text>Language Modules are used to store words and phrases that you want to learn.</text>
	    	<text>Click in the Module editor to enter the Test Item in both your own language and the foreign language.</text>
	    	<link><img id="recordIcon" src="../../icons/recordMini.png"/></link>
	    	<text>Click on the "Record Audio" tab to record the word that you have just entered.</text>
	    	<text>Add more modules as desired. You can organise your modules into folders: Right click in the Navigator view and choose New Folder...</text>
	    	<link id="startTest" style-id="left"
	    		url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/runAction?pluginId=org.thanlwinsoft.languagetest&amp;class=org.thanlwinsoft.languagetest.eclipse.wizards.StartTestAction&amp;id=org.thanlwinsoft.languagetest.StartTestAction">
	    		<text>Start a Test</text>
	    		<img id="startTestIcon" src="../../icons/startTest.png"/>
	    	</link>
	    	<text>You need to have created at least one Test Module before you can run a test.</text>
	    	<text>For more information try the Quick Tips (also called Cheatsheets, but they don't help pass language tests!)</text>
    	</group>
    </page>
</introContent>
